This paper deals with sparse signal recovery using neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on the convergence of iterative algorithms for sparse recovery. The second most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses neural networks to solve the sparse recovery problem. The third category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper includes a compressive sensing experiment on real image data. The fourth category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as the paper proposes a new weight structure for the network to achieve linear convergence. The fifth category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper discusses the use of thresholding in the network for support selection.
